fields.title: Multiply RAM[0] by RAM[1]
fields.description: Multiply RAM[0] by RAM[1] and store the result in RAM[2]. The program assumes that RAM[0] >= 0, RAM[1] >= 0, and RAM[0] * RAM[1] < 32768.

fields.title: Add RAM[0] to RAM[1]
fields.description:
Add RAM[0] to RAM[1] and put the result in RAM[2].

Input

RAM[0] = 3
RAM[1] = 4

Output

RAM[2] = 7

fields.title: Sort Array
fields.description:
An array of numbers is stored between RAM[1000] and RAM[1004] (inclusive). Sort this array in ascending order (smallest to largest).

Input

RAM[1000] = 9
RAM[1001] = 2
RAM[1002] = 5
RAM[1003] = 4
RAM[1004] = 1

Output

RAM[1000] = 1
RAM[1001] = 2
RAM[1002] = 4
RAM[1003] = 5
RAM[1004] = 9

fields.title: Subtract RAM[0] from RAM[1]
fields.description:
Subtract RAM[0] from RAM[1] and put the result in RAM[2]. Or, put another way: RAM[2] = RAM[1] - RAM[0].

Inputs

RAM[0] = 12
RAM[1] = 6

Outputs

RAM[2] = -6

fields.title: Divide RAM[0] by RAM[1]
fields.description:
Divide RAM[0] by RAM[1] and put the result in RAM[2] and the remainder in RAM[3].

Test 1

Inputs

RAM[1] = 6

Outputs

RAM[2] = 2
RAM[3] = 0

Test 2

Inputs

RAM[0] = 12
RAM[1] = 5

Outputs

RAM[2] = 2
RAM[3] = 2

fields.title: Press 'a' to make the screen black
fields.description: Pressing the 'a' key should make every pixel on the hack computer screen black. Pressing any other key (or no key) should result in nothing happening (the program should wait.)

fields.title: Search for index in sorted array
fields.description:
You are given a sorted array, from RAM[1000] to RAM[2000] (inclusive.) The number you are searching for is in RAM[0]. Write a program to add the index of that number to RAM[1].

Inputs

RAM[0] = 2403
RAM[1000] = 23
RAM[1001] = 25
...
RAM[1230] = 2297
RAM[1231] = 2403
...
RAM[2000] = 9020

Output

RAM[1] = 1231
